= Relationships
Relationships in the context of math is the connection between different elements or sets. They are usually represented in the form of Input - Output of a pair
An arrow demonstrating the relationship can point to a specific element, or an entire set containing it
== Cartesian Product:
Cartesian, often illustrated using the #sym.times ( A #sym.times B ) is the list of all possible ordered pairs between the two lists, or elements
- *NOTE:* a ordered pair is a pair that respects orders (obvious huh.), meaning (a, b) is different than (b, a)
== Other Relationship Types
There are other relationship types that serve different purposes, illustrated and demonstrated below:
- Many to One
- One to One
- One to Many
- Many to Many

